injured in clashes between Muslims and Christians in Upper
 Egypt , the Minya Security Directorate, which oversees security
for the Minya governorate, said.  Two Christians and one Muslim died after a Muslim family
and a Christian family exchanged fire today, the directorate
said in an e-mailed statement.  Egyptâ€™s last major sectarian clashes took place in May
2011. At least 12 people died and 186 were injured in fights
